    The Launch activity for the service app. Started when the app is run, provides a basic interface for starting and stopping the service.

    • Method Detail

      • startMain

        public void startMain(View view)
        Called when the "start"-button is pressed. Makes an intent, and starts the service wit parameter "stop" = false, so that the service knows that it should start, not stop.
        Parameters:
        View - - Provided by the code that calls onClick-events

      • stopMain

        public void stopMain(View view)
        Called when the "stop"-button is pressed. Builds an intent to send the message "stop" = true to the service. The intent then calls the onStartCommand()-method of the StepMainService
        Parameters:
        View - - Provided by the code that calls onClick-events
